So a high entrenchment score is a bad thing, according to these authors. High entrenchment, low Q. Low entrenchment, high Q. Entrenchment provisions here must mean provisos that are put in place to prevent positive change or reduce shareholder voting rights. So if a firm has high entrenchment, they limit shareholder rights and do not facilitate potentially risky change. \
